[assistant] Implemented and committed the native-test support needed for the `FileUtils` cache reset to execute under native image.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit:
[assistant] - `54688832f5 Register Ant FileUtils cache fields for native tests`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changed file:
[assistant] - `tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/ant-ant-tests/reflect-config.json`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - Registered `org.apache.tools.ant.util.FileUtils` cache fields:
[assistant]   - `class$java$io$File`
[assistant]   - `setLastModified`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why:
[assistant] - The existing `FileUtilsTest` resets these cached fields before calling the public `setFileLastModified(...)` API.
[assistant] - Under native image, those fields need reflection metadata so the reset can actually run and force the remaining first-time `Class#forName(...)` path.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Per instruction, I did not compile or run tests.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Note:
